Scientific Names tool comparison ¶

This notebook is part of ENVRI FAIR WP11 use case on scientific names and FAIR data. The goal is to document how different tools provide different responses for the same scientific name.

The following small test dataset (plants) were generated to highlight some of the issues.

scientificName Notes
Pinus mugo Turra Correct and accepted name
Pinus mugo Exclude the author name
Pinus mugo Smith Wrong author name
Pinus muco Turra Spelling mistake
Pino mugo Turra Wrong genus
Pinus basso Turra Wrong species

Services ¶

Global Names Resolver

http://resolver.globalnames.org/

From the Global Names Index (GNI) project which queries multiple taxonomic backbone and services. More here: https://globalnames.org/

GBIF

https://gbif.org Global Biodiveristy Information Facility Python Library

Catalogue of Life

Name-match tool https://data.catalogueoflife.org/tools/name-match

LifeWatch Data services

https://lifewatch.be/data-services/

Outputs¶

Global Names Resolver

Pinus mugo Turra

Accepted name with the binomials and author name (the person credited with the first formal use of the name)

In [1]:
import requests
from pprint import pprint
import json
from requests.structures import CaseInsensitiveDict
url = "http://resolver.globalnames.org/name_resolvers.json?names=Pinus+mugo+Turra"
headers = CaseInsensitiveDict()
headers["Accept"] = "application/json"

resp = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
# data_source_title shows the source name 
for i in json.loads(resp.text)['data']:
    pprint(i['results'])

import requests
from pprint import pprint
import json
from requests.structures import CaseInsensitiveDict
url = "http://resolver.globalnames.org/name_resolvers.json?names=Pinus+mugo"
headers = CaseInsensitiveDict()
headers["Accept"] = "application/json"

resp = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
# data_source_title shows the source name 
for i in json.loads(resp.text)['data']:
    pprint(i['results'])

import requests
from pprint import pprint
import json
from requests.structures import CaseInsensitiveDict
url = "http://resolver.globalnames.org/name_resolvers.json?names=Pinus+mugo+Smith"
headers = CaseInsensitiveDict()
headers["Accept"] = "application/json"

resp = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
# data_source_title shows the source name 
for i in json.loads(resp.text)['data']:
    pprint(i['results'])

import requests
from pprint import pprint
import json
from requests.structures import CaseInsensitiveDict
url = "http://resolver.globalnames.org/name_resolvers.json?names=Pinus+muco+Turra"
headers = CaseInsensitiveDict()
headers["Accept"] = "application/json"

resp = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
# data_source_title shows the source name 
for i in json.loads(resp.text)['data']:
    pprint(i['results'])

LifeWatch¶

LifeWatch Taxon match service:

https://lifewatch.be/data-services/

For this tool, you will need to login and submit a job. There are several different Taxon backbone and services can be selected at the same time. No API. This tool let's you select different backbone such as GNI, IPNI. After the job runs, the result is presented the following way:

A few other services to compare¶

NomenMatch¶

A few other web friendly tools http://match.taibif.tw/about.html "NomenMatch is a tool for taxonomists to match a set of species names against other sets with certain authority. It returns matched names, ids, usage status, and links to original sources. So not only the matched results, users can also know about differences of name usage among different sources. This is important because we believe that there is no absolute right or wrong, and only different perspectives in taxonomy. This tool provides easily references for taxonomists."

Test query link: http://match.taibif.tw/api.php?names=Pinus%20mugo%20Turra|Pinus%20mugo%20Smith|Vicia%20faba%20L.|Vicia%20faba%20S.|Vicia%20faba|Vicia%20fava

Taxonomic name resolution service¶

2013 paper https://dx.doi.org/10.1186%2F1471-2105-14-16

https://tnrs.biendata.org/#

This has a score but uses different backbone

EU-NOMEN¶

EU-NOMEN/PESI project http://www.eu-nomen.eu/portal/index.php

EU-nomen enables the correct use of species names and their classification, to more accurately manage information on animals and plants. This is the first all-taxa inventory for European species.

In [24]:
import requests
from requests.structures import CaseInsensitiveDict
url = "http://www.eu-nomen.eu/portal/rest/PESIRecordsByName/Vicia%20Faba?like=true&offset=1"
headers = CaseInsensitiveDict()
headers["Accept"] = "application/json"


resp = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(resp.status_code)

200

Comparison Table¶

Comparison of some of the tools mentioned above.

scientificName Global Names Resolver CoL GBIF LifeWatch
Pinus mugo Turra Exact match, Score: 0.988 Provides several matches from different databases exact Exact match. returns one results Exact match
Pinus mugo Smith (incorrect authority) Disregards the authority string and matches against "Pinus mugo" canonical No result. No match found
Vicia faba L. Exact match. Provides several matches from different databases variant Exact match. returns one results No match found
Vicia faba S. (incorrect authority) Disregards the authority string canonical No result No match found
Vicia faba Exact match, Score: 0.988. Also finds Vicia faba L. exact Returns several results Exact match
Vicia fava (spelling mistake) Fuzzy canonical match, none No result No match found
